.TH VMSWARM 1 "May 2026" "1.0" "VMSwarm Manual"
.SH NAME
vmswarm \- KVM/libvirt VM orchestration framework
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vmswarm
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
VMSwarm is a bash-first CLI tool to spin up, manage, and orchestrate multiple KVM virtual machines using libvirt/virsh. Supports parallel execution via subshell, fork (C), or threads (C).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h
Show short help message.
.TP
.BR \-f
Fork-based parallel execution (C binary).
.TP
.BR \-t
Thread-based parallel execution (C binary).
.TP
.BR \-s
Subshell execution.
.TP
.BR \-l " " \fIdir\fR
Set log directory (default: /var/log/vmswarm).
.TP
.BR \-r
Restore config defaults (root only).
.TP
.BR \-v
Verbose output.
.TP
.BR \-n " " \fIcount\fR
Number of VMs for batch create.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B create
Provision a new KVM VM (from ISO or qcow2 import). Prompts for missing parameters.
.TP
.B start
Start VM(s).
.TP
.B stop
Graceful shutdown of VM(s).
.TP
.B kill
Force-off VM(s).
.TP
.B pause
Suspend VM(s) in memory.
.TP
.B resume
Resume paused VM(s).
.TP
.B suspend
Save VM state to disk.
.TP
.B delete
Undefine and remove VM(s) [requires root].
.TP
.B ps
List VMs with state, RAM, CPUs, tags, IP.
.TP
.B info
Detailed info for VM(s).
.TP
.B ssh
SSH into VM(s).
.TP
.B run
Execute a local script on VM(s) via SSH.
.TP
.B clone
Clone an existing VM.
.TP
.B tag
Add/remove/list tags.
.TP
.B snap
Manage snapshots (take/list/restore/delete).
.TP
.B net
Manage libvirt networks (list/create/delete).
.TP
.B export
Export VM to portable archive.
.TP
.B import
Import VM from archive.
.TP
.B logs
Read and filter the vmswarm log file.
.SH TARGET SYNTAX
.TP
.B <name>
By VM name: worker-1
.TP
.B <id>
By numeric ID: 3
.TP
.B <id1>-<id2>
ID range: 1-5
.TP
.B id:<n,m,k>
Explicit IDs: id:1,3,7
.TP
.B tag:<name>
By tag: tag:dev
.TP
.B all
All registered VMs
.SH EXAMPLES
.B vmswarm -s -n 3 create --name node --tag cluster --import base.qcow2
.PP
.B vmswarm ps --tag cluster
.PP
.B vmswarm -f run tag:cluster --script deploy.sh
.PP
.B vmswarm -t start 1-10
.PP
.B vmswarm snap take all --name pre-update
.PP
.B vmswarm export worker-1 --out /backups
.PP
.B vmswarm logs --tail 50 --grep ERROR
.SH ERROR CODES
100 Unknown option, 101 Missing parameter, 102 VM not found, 103 Tool missing, 104 Permission denied, 105 File not found, 106 SSH failed, 107 Script not found, 108 Tag not found, 109 Snapshot not found, 110 Binary missing, 111 KVM module not loaded, 112 libvirtd not running, 113 Network exists, 114 Clone source missing, 115 Archive corrupted
